# Tailwind JIT — Responsive Layouts

**Goal:** Use Tailwind CSS with Just-In-Time compilation for responsive, interactive layouts.

---

## Core Concept

```tsx
// ✅ Use className for responsive layouts
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <div className="hover:bg-primary transition-colors duration-200">
    Content
  </div>
</div>

// ❌ Don't use for static inline styles
<div style={twsx('p-4')}>Content</div>
```

---

## Usage Patterns

### Responsive Grid
```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  {/* Mobile: 1 column */}
  {/* Tablet: 2 columns */}
  {/* Desktop: 3 columns */}
</div>
```

### Responsive Flex
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">
  {/* Mobile: vertical stack */}
  {/* Desktop: horizontal layout */}
</div>
```

### Responsive Spacing
```tsx
<div className="p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">
  {/* Small padding on mobile, larger on desktop */}
</div>
```

### Interactive States
```tsx
<button className="bg-primary hover:bg-primary/80 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary/50 transition-colors duration-200">
  Click me
</button>
```

