## When to Use className

### ✅ Responsive Layouts
```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3" />
```

### ✅ Hover/Focus States
```tsx
<div className="hover:bg-primary focus:ring-2 transition-colors" />
```

### ✅ Animations & Transitions
```tsx
<div className="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out" />
```

### ✅ Complex Styling Logic
```tsx
<div className={cn(
  "base-styles",
  variant === "primary" && "primary-styles",
  isDisabled && "disabled-styles"
)} />
```

---

## When to Use twsx()

### ✅ Simple Inline Styles
```tsx
<div style={twsx('p-4 m-2 bg-primary')} />
```

### ✅ Dynamic Styles
```tsx
<div style={twsx(`p-${spacing}`)} />
```

### ✅ Module-Level Styles
```tsx
const styles = { card: twsx('p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm') };
<div style={styles.card} />
```

